00:40:54.040 --> 00:40:58.700
This testimony shows that the
police rounded up prostitutes not

00:40:58.700 --> 00:41:03.730 position:56%
for the suppression of prostitution,
but for the control of STD's,

00:41:03.730 --> 00:41:09.390
even though the prohibitionist
rule justified the roundups.

00:41:09.390 --> 00:41:13.680
It also demonstrates that the
human rights of the women detained

00:41:13.680 --> 00:41:20.730
at the STD detention treatment
centers were severely violated.

00:41:20.730 --> 00:41:25.650 position:56%
Other former military prostitutes
also testified that forced treatment

00:41:25.650 --> 00:41:28.460
in detention centers was painful,

00:41:28.460 --> 00:41:32.140
even causing death due
to penicillin shock.

00:41:32.140 --> 00:41:35.290
The contact tracing program
and forced treatment were

00:41:35.290 --> 00:41:40.850
so mercilessly carried out that
its subjects were terrorized.

00:41:40.850 --> 00:41:45.520 position:56%
For instance, if an American soldier
pointed out a woman as a carrier

00:41:45.520 --> 00:41:51.500
of STD's, she was immediately
apprehended and incarcerated

00:41:51.500 --> 00:41:54.940
at detention center,
regardless of whether

00:41:54.940 --> 00:41:57.980
or not she actually infected him.

00:41:57.980 --> 00:42:04.660 position:56%
The Korean officials and camp town
women, often called the [inaudible],

00:42:04.660 --> 00:42:09.800
which means clearing the
enemies in Korean, took them.

00:42:10.830 --> 00:42:13.000
Then how was the Korean
government able

00:42:13.000 --> 00:42:16.960
to implement those two
seemingly contradictory policies

00:42:16.960 --> 00:42:21.870
of prohibition and regulation
simultaneously in the form

00:42:21.870 --> 00:42:24.140 position:56%
of the toleration regulation regime?

00:42:24.140 --> 00:42:27.770
In fact, prohibition was
based on laws that were passed

00:42:27.770 --> 00:42:33.960
by the legislature while regulation
was implemented through rules,

00:42:33.960 --> 00:42:39.210 position:56%
orders and local ordinances that
the other administrators could enact

00:42:39.210 --> 00:42:42.750
without the legislature's
rectification.

00:42:42.750 --> 00:42:46.690
In this system, regulation
of prohibition

00:42:46.690 --> 00:42:48.700
and in turn both the regulation

00:42:48.700 --> 00:42:53.030
and prohibition suspended
basic rights guaranteed

00:42:53.030 --> 00:42:57.360
by the constitution,
such as arrest warrants,

00:42:57.360 --> 00:43:02.030
the right of legal counsel
and the right to trial.

00:43:03.070 --> 00:43:06.530
The Korean Constitution
specifies that the restriction

00:43:06.530 --> 00:43:11.740
of personal freedom
should be based on law.

00:43:11.740 --> 00:43:15.440
Therefore in principle
the STD control

00:43:15.440 --> 00:43:19.780
in the camp towns violated
the constitution.

00:43:19.780 --> 00:43:24.160 position:56%
Borrowing from the Italian political
philosopher Giorgi Agamben,

00:43:24.160 --> 00:43:28.910
I think this legal structure
can be conceptualized as a state

00:43:28.910 --> 00:43:33.950
of exemption in that it
represents the undercutting of laws

00:43:33.950 --> 00:43:37.580
by executive actions,
causing disturbance

00:43:37.580 --> 00:43:41.910
in the hierarchy of
laws and regulations.

00:43:41.910 --> 00:43:44.870
Under this regime the
Korean government attempted

00:43:44.870 --> 00:43:49.550
